## Open Questions / Next Steps

- How does this integrate with an agent's action system? (e.g., "pursue water" needs
  to map to actual pathfinding/task selection)
- Should there be hysteresis (sticky priorities) to prevent rapid switching?
- Could tier multipliers themselves be dynamic based on agent personality traits?
- How do environmental factors (proximity to resources, danger) factor in alongside
  this internal priority score?
- What role does this play in the larger "modular, isolated behavior state" goal?
